arts.ttl: Welsh side Wrexham opens its Down Under tour with a 3-0 win over A-League’s Melbourne Victory
arts.sum: Welsh soccer side Wrexham opened a three-match tour of Australia and New Zealand on Friday without their high-profile co-owners Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney making the trip Down Under. Playing in Australia and New Zealand — after recent preseason tours to the United States — is part of an effort to spread Wrexham’s global footprint which has been enhanced by the popular “Welcome to Wrexham” fly-on-the-wall TV documentary.
